---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Food Words Valid in Scrabble — International Cuisine List"
  description="Explore food and cooking words valid in Scrabble. From TOFU to GYOZA, master international food terms with point values, origins, and gameplay strategy."
  keywords="food words scrabble, cooking words scrabble, tofu scrabble points, international food scrabble, valid food words, naan scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Food Words Valid in Scrabble — International Cuisine List",
    "description": "Master international food words valid in Scrabble with point values and strategy tips.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-14",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/food-words-scrabble" }
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is TOFU a valid Scrabble word?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes! TOFU is valid in both TWL and SOWPODS, scoring 7 points (T=1, O=1, F=4, U=1). Many international food terms have been adopted into the official Scrabble dictionaries as they entered common English usage." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What food words score the most in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "SCHMALTZ scores 24 points, GYOZA scores 18 points, and KIMCHI scores 17 points. International food terms often contain high-value letters like Z, K, and Y that boost their scores significantly." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is NAAN a valid Scrabble word?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes! NAAN is valid in both TWL and SOWPODS, scoring 4 points (N=1, A=1, A=1, N=1). Both NAAN and NAN are accepted spellings. It's useful for balancing a vowel-heavy rack since it uses two A tiles." }
      }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Food Words</span>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Food Words Valid in Scrabble — International Cuisine List</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-14">June 14, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>5 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">
        International cuisine has enriched the Scrabble dictionary with dozens of playable food words. From Japanese TOFU and GYOZA to Indian GHEE and NAAN, French ROUX and AIOLI — these culinary terms are now legitimate scoring weapons. Many contain unusual letter combinations that opponents won't challenge, and several feature high-value tiles.
      </p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">60+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid Food Words</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">24 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Highest (SCHMALTZ)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">18 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Best 5-Letter (GYOZA)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">8+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Languages Represented</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top 18 Food Words for Scrabble</h2>
      <p>These international food terms are all valid in official Scrabble dictionaries. Ranked by point value, they cover cuisines from around the world.</p>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
          <thead class="bg-gray-800">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Word</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Points</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Letters</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Origin</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-800">
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">SCHMALTZ</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">24</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">8</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Yiddish (rendered fat)</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">GYOZA</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">18</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Japanese (dumplings)</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">KIMCHI</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">17</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Korean (fermented veg)</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">QUINOA</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">15</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Quechua (grain)</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">KEBAB</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">13</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Arabic (grilled meat)</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">FALAFEL</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">13</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Arabic (chickpea fritter)</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">HUMMUS</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">13</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Arabic (chickpea dip)</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">WASABI</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">11</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Japanese (hot paste)</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">ROUX</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">11</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">4</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">French (sauce base)</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">PANKO</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">11</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Japanese (breadcrumbs)</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">GOULASH</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">11</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Hungarian (stew)</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">PILAF</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">10</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Turkish (rice dish)</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">TAHINI</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">9</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Arabic (sesame paste)</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">SUSHI</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">8</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Japanese (rice dish)</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">GHEE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">8</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">4</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Hindi (clarified butter)</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">TOFU</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">4</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Japanese (bean curd)</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">PESTO</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Italian (basil sauce)</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">AIOLI</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Provençal (garlic mayo)</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Food Words by Cuisine Origin</h2>
      <p>International food terms have been steadily added to Scrabble dictionaries as they enter common English usage. Here's a breakdown by culinary tradition.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🍣 Japanese</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">TOFU (7), MISO (6), GYOZA (18), WASABI (11), PANKO (11), RAMEN (7), SUSHI (8)</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🥘 Middle Eastern</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">TAHINI (9), FALAFEL (13), HUMMUS (13), PITA (6), KEBAB (13)</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🇫🇷 French</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">ROUX (11), AIOLI (5), CREPE (9), BRIE (6), QUICHE (20)</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🇮🇳 South Asian</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">GHEE (8), NAAN (4), PILAF (10), RAITA (5), DAL (4)</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Why Food Words Are Great for Scrabble</h2>
      <p>Food terminology offers unique advantages in competitive play. Many food words use unusual letter combinations that create parallel play opportunities and are less likely to be challenged.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-cyan-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Scoring Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Food words often feature <span class="text-white font-medium">high-value letters in short packages</span>. GYOZA packs G(2)+Y(4)+O(1)+Z(10)+A(1) = 18 points in just 5 letters. ROUX delivers R(1)+O(1)+U(1)+X(8) = 11 points in 4 letters. Efficient scoring machines.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy Tips</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">GYOZA is a Z powerhouse:</span> At 18 points for 5 common letters, GYOZA is one of the best Z plays in the game. Opponents rarely know it's valid, so challenges work in your favor.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">ROUX dumps X efficiently:</span> At 11 points for just 4 letters, ROUX is one of the best ways to play X without needing uncommon rack combinations. R, O, U are all common tiles.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Vowel dumps with food words:</span> AIOLI uses 4 vowels in 5 letters — perfect for unloading a vowel-heavy rack. NAAN dumps two A tiles. These keep you scoring while rebalancing.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Challenge-proof vocabulary:</span> Food words are real English dictionary entries — they won't be successfully challenged. QUINOA, KIMCHI, WASABI are all in official tournament word lists.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">GHEE for the double-E dump:</span> At 8 points with G(2)+H(4)+E(1)+E(1), GHEE lets you play two E tiles plus the H tile in one compact word. Excellent rack management play.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Related Articles -->
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/best-z-words-scrabble" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best Z Words in Scrabble — Top Scoring Z Plays</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/best-q-words-scrabble" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best Q Words in Scrabble — Top Scoring Q Plays</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/highest-scoring-scrabble-words" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Highest Scoring Scrabble Words Ever — Ultimate List</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-blue-800/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Try our free Scrabble Word Finder — instant results, no signup</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-400 text-gray-950 text-sm font-semibold transition-colors">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
